t arises a Higgs mass coincidence problem,\nwhy the ratios $\\rho_t,\\rho_{Wt}$ are so close to one, can we find a mechanism\nthat naturally gives $m_H^2=m_Z m_t$, $2m_H= m_W+m_t$?.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Sep 2012 20:06:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Sep 2012 20:00:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 4 Mar 2014 21:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-06"}
